docs/ROADMAP.md:110:The project is drifting when the main output is a new internal viewer, archive, schema, handoff shape, safety layer, or lifecycle report that does not help a task move from intake to verified result to human decision.
docs/ROADMAP.md:112:The project is on course when a real task can enter the factory, be decomposed, run in isolated execution contexts, produce evidence, pass or fail checks honestly, and return a short owner-ready decision report.
docs/CURRENT_STATE.md:5:RunForge is currently a local, deterministic, artifact-first engineering harness. It can collect evidence, run bounded checks, classify failures, produce proposal/readiness packets, render packet views, record operator decisions, and preserve handoff/archive evidence. It is not yet a complete Agent OS / Task Factory because it has not proven one end-to-end task run.
